task.summary:
Initial commit. IntelliJ project created.
Hotel class created with name property and getter/setter methods.

Added list of rooms to Hotel class and getter.
Added Room class.

Added Room superclass with list of guests and room capacity property.
Added Guest class with name property.
Added Bedroom subclass of Room. This has bedroomNumber field. Added a getter for bedroomNumber field.

Created RoomType enum to hold information about the type of bedroom and its capacity.
Added RoomType to Bedroom class and put in getter for this.

Added Conference room subclass of room and name field plus getter and setter.
Added DiningRoom subclass of room.
Added rate field to Bedroom class and getter/setter.
Added chargeable Boolean to Room superclass to indicate whether the room is chargeable.
Added another constructor to Room that takes in only capacity as certain subclasses will not need to use this not all are chargeable.
Added separate lists for the different Room types to Hotel class. Added getters for these lists.

Added chargeable boolean parameter to ConferenceRoom constructor as conference rooms are chargeable types of room.
Remove boolean chargeable from DiningRoom constructor as this is not a chargeable type of room.
Created manageBedrooms method to Hotel class to manage the list of bedrooms that are available. It has the capability to add or remove rooms from the list of bedrooms that the Hotel maintains. This will be used in the check in/check out process to add to or remove the available rooms.
Added checkInGuests method and helper method called findAvailableRoomForGuests. The check in method uses the availability checker to identify whether there is availability and if so returns the room that can be filled.
Created addGuestToRoom method in the Room superclass.
